Senegal to Spend $70 Million on Fuel Storage, Quotidien Says

-- B y   R o s e   S k e l t o n
-- 
2011-08-03T13:47:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/senegal-to-spend-70-million-on-fuel-storage-quotidien-says.html
Senegal  will spend 32 billion  CFA
francs  ($70 million) to expand fuel-storage facilities in the
West African nation, Sud Quotidien reported, citing Abdoulaye
Ndiaye, director-general of Senegalaise de Stockage.  Storage capacity will be expanded to 300,000 cubic meters
(10.6 million cubic feet), from 167,000 cubic meters now, the
Dakar-based newspaper  reported . The local units of Societe
Generale SA and BNP Paribas SA as well as Banque Islamique au
 Senegal  financed the loan for the storage company, according to
the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rose Skelton in Dakar via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 